headline: Wells Fargo Shares Rally Most Since Trump Won the Election
summary: The stock climbed to close 7.1% higher Tuesday, its biggest daily gain since last Nov. 6, when Donald Trump’s election win boosted financial stocks with expectations the president would ease regulation and juice the economy with his agenda.  Tuesday’s surge made Wells Fargo the day’s best performer in the KBW Bank Index.  For the past month, Wells Fargo is behind only Comerica Inc., whose shares were boosted by its planned acquisition by Fifth Third Bancorp in the largest bank deal of 2025.

headline: Wells Fargo Boosts Key Profit Metric as Asset Cap Removed
summary: The projection comes as the San Francisco-based bank reported net interest income that slightly missed analysts’ estimates.  NII — the difference between what the company earns on lending and pays for deposits — totaled $11.95 billion in the third quarter, compared with analysts’ expectations of $12.01 billion.  “We still continue to believe this is one of the best franchises in the country with breadth across both the consumer and commercial products that very few can match,” Chief Financial Officer Mike Santomassimo said on a conference call with reporters Tuesday.
